//Culturally, this pays homage to 3001 and 3005, the lone voice lost in space and the obvious Fifthist pinkness. Despite that it's in a way an interesting reversal of 3001 by having the focus take place largely before the ejection-into-foreign-space event. Overall, I'd say the strength of this work is establishing Bartleman before giving us the pathos-laden final series of transmissions. The character comes off as well-rounded, having a logical motive to go into space.//
